<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07868</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A NATIONAL FILM MUSEUM AND EXHIBITION PARK, PROVIDING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to establish a National Film Museum and Exhibition Park that shall serve as a center for communication and development of all stakeholders of the industry, serve as an exhibition and incubation site for Filipino films, serve as a site for global film festivals, and a one stop shop for concerns relating to the Film Industry.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “National Film Museum and Exhibition Park Act of 2017.” </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BELARO, SALVADOR JR. B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-06-13</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-08-07)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC INFORMATION ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>